    "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index Acceptance Requirement",
    "requirementText": "The CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) for the candidate centrifugal blood pump shall not exceed RH < 10 under any of the five evaluated flow-speed operating conditions, demonstrating non-inferiority to the predicate device.",
    "rationale": "The RH threshold of 10 is specified to ensure the candidate pump does not produce clinically unacceptable hemolysis levels relative to the predicate device. This criterion was derived from the 510(k) substantial equivalence framework for Class II CPB devices."
